-- Inmarsat Shares Drop Most Since August After Harbinger Capital Cuts Stake
-- B y   M a t t h e w   C a m p b e l l
-- 2010-10-05T16:02:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/inmarsat-shares-drop-most-since-august-after-harbinger-capital-cuts-stake.html
Inmarsat Plc  fell the most in more
than a month in London after  Philip Falconeâ€™s  Harbinger Capital
Partners sold about half of its 28 percent holding and ruled
out making an offer for the rest of the company.  Inmarsat shares slid 4 percent to 629 pence, the biggest
drop since Aug. 19. The stock has fallen 9.1 percent this year,
valuing the operator of satellite communications systems at
about 2.9 billion pounds ($4.6 billion).  Harbinger today said it had sold 14 percent of Inmarsat,
or 65 million ordinary shares, for 410 million pounds.
Yesterday the New York-based hedge fund ended speculation that
it would make a bid for all of Inmarsat by ruling out a
takeover attempt.  Harbinger and U.S. satellite company SkyTerra
Communications Inc. considered a full takeover of Inmarsat in
2008, seeking to combine satellite holdings and offer services
for mobile Internet.  To contact the reporter on this story:
